title: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: The All types dialog in JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (e.g., a, a1, b, c, d) which are currently displayed prominently.
OB: The All types dialog shows obfuscated classes prominently.
EB: The obfuscated classes should be displayed less prominently to avoid confusion and improve user experience.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Open the All types dialog in JDK 1.4.
2. Observe the obfuscated classes being displayed prominently.
